The President met with members of the Congressional Black Caucus (CBC) to discuss job creation and economic growth. The President acknowledged that while the economy has added jobs, many American families are still struggling, especially African Americans. The President emphasized his commitment to supporting economic policies that help those most affected. The meeting also addressed the economic challenges faced by young people, and the President highlighted initiatives aimed at providing relief and job opportunities for low-income youth. Additionally, the President mentioned Domestic Policy Initiatives, such as Growth Zones, which provide tax incentives for investment and employment, and streamlined access to government assistance for economically distressed areas. These initiatives aim to rejuvenate the hardest-hit areas of the country.